"#preanalitica","#rete-di-laboratori"],"status":"developing","address":"c-000047","source_type":"guideline","author":"SIPMeL - Commissione Nazionale Qualità ed Accreditamento (COMMQUA) + GdS-VEA + GdS-MS","date_published":"2019-10-07","url":"","confidence":"high","key_claims":["Documento Q12-BC1 (v1.0, approvato in Consiglio Nazionale a Riva del Garda il 7 ottobre 2019): recepimento italiano di ISO/TS 20658:2017 (raccolta, trasporto, ricezione e trattamento dei campioni), applicato ai punti di prelievo e ai laboratori in rete.","Premessa: la rete dei servizi di medicina di laboratorio cambia rapidamente — aumentano i punti di prelievo e le stazioni POCT, diminuiscono i centri che eseguono la fase analitica; spesso uno stesso punto prelievi serve più laboratori, gestiti da titolari diversi.","ISO/TS 20658 si applica solo ai processi pre-esame legati alla gestione dei campioni (raccolta, trasporto, ricezione, conservazione), non a tutti i processi pre-esame di ISO 15189 (es. informazioni per pazienti e modulo di richiesta restano in capo al laboratorio esecutore).","Infrastrutture: il punto prelievi deve garantire spazio adeguato, ergonomia, privacy, pulizia/disinfezione quotidiana e dispositivi di primo soccorso adeguati (incluso, per raccomandazione SIPMeL, un defibrillatore e barella ad altezza regolabile).","Identificazione paziente/campione: ISO 20658 richiede almeno due identificatori; SIPMeL segnala una incongruenza interna alla norma (11.1 vs 12.2) e ritiene più praticabile l'approccio EFLM (nome + data di nascita + identificativo aggiuntivo, bracciale per i ricoverati).","Raccolta del campione: consenso informato, sequenza di prelievo (emocoltura, coagulazione, siero, eparina, EDTA...), limiti di volume per pazienti pediatrici (1-10% del volume ematico totale secondo finestra temporale), criteri per prelievo capillare in adulti e neonati.","Accettazione/rifiuto dei campioni è prerogativa del laboratorio esecutore, non del punto prelievi; SIPMeL raccomanda che il rifiuto non sia una decisione meccanica ma una valutazione ponderata rischi/benefici per il paziente, documentata.","SIPMeL raccomanda particolare attenzione all'infrastruttura informatica (interfacce di richiesta gestite da fornitori esterni ai punti prelievo) e alla supervisione/audit interni sui sistemi di etichettatura automatizzata (label broker)."]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[]},"smart_blocks:Wiki/sources/SIPMeL - Accreditamento Punti di Prelievo e Laboratori in Rete.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"am2aod","at":1781675958514},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.08030143,0.02932611,-0.0407554,0.04328476,-0.00753087,-0.04199427,-0.04408469,0.01613806,0.02624457,0.02605244,-0.06538505,-0.10606887,0.00090222,0.04735181,0.01827151,-0.04654607,0.0139209,0.02426925,0.03314922,-0.02795839,0.14194609,-0.03666259,-0.01253371,-0.07576411,0.05117279,-0.00999774,-0.00151477,-0.04917656,-0.02984172,-0.20280808,0.01279515,0.00588499,-0.01748945,-0.03388751,0.04515781,0.02067206,-0.04056353,0.0902459,0.00015508,0.00979763,0.04874285,0.02995714,-0.02885314,-0.00188891,-0.01209761,-0.02008783,-0.03823313,0.05326106,-0.01840808,-0.04130725,-0.0223534,0.05711215,-0.00232585,0.05112373,0.02992295,0.01596316,0.05552636,0.01258332,0.07614863,0.08271779,0.0713352,0.01123879,-0.26167822,0.04229792,0.00042048,0.02007174,-0.07897572,0.00697235,-0.06552035,-0.01633228,-0.06339072,-0.06721984,-0.00748198,0.02269395,0.05132881,-0.03786431,0.02263865,0.05541262,-0.01509824,0.01766858,-0.00180713,0.0511211,-0.0311197,-0.01038546,-0.01528234,-0.02991814,0.0371337,0.04287697,0.0322866,-0.01785714,-0.05055882,-0.05234899,0.05076504,0.06409714,-0.00147589,0.01296628,-0.01310247,0.05688774,-0.05597421,0.07505818,-0.06397785,-0.0212555,-0.01510753,0.02320594,-0.006354,0.09346171,-0.03318113,-0.02836128,-0.01105674,0.05539268,0.0072979,-0.02821057,0.06770903,-0.04158133,-0.01648808,0.00722219,0.01438677,-0.00986797,0.00646087,0.00933609